The primary objective is to demonstrate rifaximin 200-mg tablets (test) and Xifaxan(R) 200 mg tablets (reference ) are clinically bioequivalent with respect to the clinical cure rates when administered 3 times a day (TID) for 3 days in subjects with travelers' diarrhea.

